A giant crane broke free from a skyscraper, crashing into residential buildings on Manhattan's East Side, resulting in at least two deaths.
Witnesses described the terrifying scene as the crane headed towards their windows.
Mayor Bloomberg confirmed four fatalities and ten injuries, attributing the accident to safety concerns raised by residents.
The rescue operation was challenging, with one man rescued from the rubble after hours.
Complaints about construction practices were reported prior to the incident, highlighting the risks associated with the city's building boom and the need for stricter safety measures.
